Obese child's menu: doesn't eat breakfast and eats sausages
More than a third of children aged 9 to 13 have overweight problems, with 9% of schoolchildren being overweight and 5% obese.
The obese children usually come from families with unhealthy lifestyles, as the current survey has shown.
It once again shows how important it is for the healthy development of the human environment in which he grows up and the patterns he is surrounded by.
For example, sausages appear on tables in obese children up to half as often as in families of children with normal weight.
Fried fries had for dinner the day before the research related to an educational event called Obesity is not a coincidence of more than 19 percent obese.
In fat families, it is also not customary to sport, but this concerns most of the families of today's schoolchildren - only 15% of children have responded that their parents will find time for active movement at least once a week.
Research among 900 children
The survey took place at the end of last year and was attended by nearly 900 children from primary schools from all over the Czech Republic.
It was already the second year of Obesita's event, not a coincidence, supported by the General Health Insurance and Unilever.
Up to now, more than 12,000 schoolchildren from the 4th to 8th classes have been involved in the project.
Good eating and sufficient family exercise is one of the determining factors that causes a dramatically increasing number of overweight or even obesity children.
"Only half of the enquires, for example, stated that she has five times a day in the breakfast-snack-lunch-snack-dinner mode, which is one of the basic assumptions of proper nutrition," one of the results of the survey is.
No breakfast and no evening sausage
Experts point out that relative details are important for healthy development, such as regular family breakfast time.
In the Czech Republic, only 23 percent of school children eat breakfast at the same time.
In most families, everyone eats breakfast alone.
And the worst part was finding out that you don't eat breakfast at all in ten households.
Breakfast is the basis of a proper daily diet.
The questionnaire showed that in the families of obese children, unhealthy fries are consumed much more often.
Almost everyone - regardless of weight - drinks sweet lemonade every day (70 percent).
Although more than 40 per cent of the children questioned regularly, the result was less than half - 15 per cent for their parents.
Build your diet
Another part of the survey allowed selected children (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) to build their own diet according to their own tastes and opinions.
"The eating preferences of Czech children aged 12 to 15 are far from ideal in terms of healthy nutrition."
Among their favorite dishes are a lot of flour, meat and sweet dishes.
"In particular, the great popularity of sweet sodas is alarming," is stated in the final survey report.
For lunch as a main dish, pasta won just above the poultry.
Children, however, practically did not want pulses at all, and the popularity of fish and lunch vegetable dishes is also low.
Addendum to health
At the same time, research has shown that children are willing to adjust their eating habits if they get the right information.
"In many cases, there has been a significant shift in preferences towards the principles of healthy nutrition for a group of survey participants who filled out a questionnaire after the end of the Obesita awareness lecture," stated in the results of the project.
For example, it was very distinctive with sweet sodas, where more children would start to prefer ordinary water.
Children also checked poultry and fish as the main meal of the day in the questionnaire much more often and would limit sweet meals and dumplings.
