How to recognise a lie
A glimpse of recent headlines suggests how serious and ubiquitous lies and deceptions are in everyday life.
Republican presidential candidate Herman Cain has his hands full with allegations that he sexually harassed several women - both sides claim that the other is lying.
The administrators at Penn State University were charged with perjury when they tried to hide records that a retired football coach sexually assaulted a boy.
