Park or mountains?
The architects have gathered on the occasion of a trial that carries more than controversy about royalties.
The municipal tender for 16 gates again opens up a debate about the role of Collserola Park in Barcelona.
In the mid-1980s, at the time of the greatest boom of the already extinct Corporate Metropolitana de Barcelona (CMB), this self-government printed several pamphlets to support the Collserola Park.
The flyer defined the mountain as a large park of metropolitan Barcelona.
What's more, it was supplemented by a numerical comparison with Central Park, New York.
After CMB disappeared in 1987, the park returned to the mind of many as the upper border of Barcelona. Catalan metropolis is one of the few that are not oriented north - south - but up (mountain) - down (sea).
The qualification of Collserola as a natural park goes in this direction.
The reference was no longer Central Park, but Yellowstone with wild boars instead of Yogi Bear.
This was the position until September when City Hall announced a mega contest consisting of 16 auditions for the same number of entry gates to Collserola.
The gate, of course, records the idea of the park.
It's either this or someone's trying to put the gate in the field.
So there's only one question: Collserola, park or mountain?
During the competition, both in terms of purely organisational and reflection on the city, this issue becomes the central theme of all of Barcelona's architects.
It is already a subject as ominous as when two members of this old caste chosen to meet in the elevator shake hands.
And it was this act that triggered one of the rare events between what three Barcelona architects and university professors think.
Miguel Roldan, Daniel Modol and Marta Bayon: the selection procedure has its merits.
According to Roldan, after the question of the Gulf Party began, "the" mountain side "must also be discussed, so Ildefons Cerd's speech on green apples was not followed to the end.
"We must base ourselves on the principle that Barcelona's most spacious park is the beach.
Among other things, its great availability.
Collserola is more complex, "said the architect, for whom the name" gate to Collserola "carries a" lexicological trap ": we must not imagine them" as entrances to the park, but rather as delineation of zones where it can be applied. "
Modol, like Roldan and Bayon, with experience in the world of urbanism qualifies the proposal as a "intellectual challenge" offering "some dangers."
The danger arising from the "uncertainty now posed by the public place project" after the experience of the 1980s, which had "its swan singing" in the Forum area.
The first concern is the very delimitation of borders where it should be built.
"To define something means to take the next step," that is, in principle, to take a step further.
"The new urban and planning instruments should be remembered, because the current ones (referring to the General Metropolitan Plan (PGM)) can cause a real disaster."
If we focus more closely on the question, Modol believes that the bottom slope of Collserola can be "considered a park," but not the Barcelona part, for purely topographical reasons.
Modol also recalled that there was already work done by Patronat de Collserola, which "must not end up in a junkyard," although he welcomes the fact that the City Hall offers its grémie that it will intervene in the project from "the first moment."
Moreover, he understands that the proximity of the mountain and the city is a kind of pass that allows architects to get involved in the debate, but he "doubts" that it should be this technical profile, which will lead the multidisciplinary teams ("it's all about skill," he adds) that needs to be created: "Architects should only be tools."
Bayona suggests that the answer to the question that gave the name of this game is complex, because there is no global vision of Collserol in the tender documents: "16 competitions have been announced that deal with all the axis of the mountain - sea, but there is no longitudinal study that would look at the area and understand it as a whole."
This causes at least him to sign up for all 16 tenders.
Otherwise, the project of one gate may come across the concept and definition of the architect of the adjacent gate.
In his view, the City Hall should ensure that the zone located immediately above Ronda de Dalt should ensure the full length of the equipment zone, ensuring a smooth transition between the city and the greenery.
